      "message": "1. I assume (slot-\u003esize \u003d\u003d 0) is equivalent to (slot-\u003eflags \u0026 HAX_RAM_INFO_INVALID). If so, we could simplify things by never using HAX_RAM_INFO_INVALID for slot-\u003eflags. That way, we can tell if a slot is valid just by looking at its size (when size \u003d\u003d 0, the slot is invalid, no matter what its flags says). Also, we can initialize a new slot with all zeroes. Ideally we should make the SET_RAM2 API drop the HAX_RAM_INFO_INVALID flag too, so we can delete/invalidate a slot by its id and by specifying size \u003d 0.\n2. nit: Break this long statement into 2 lines.",
