        "id": 1057369
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-22T04:24:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think you meant \u0027\u003e\u0027 instead. But actually, (mem-\u003esize \u003c size) is possible, too - imagine a new region (area) with a really big size, which overlaps with multiple existing slots (Frank has given a good example below).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 156,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 156,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "a411d8ef278aa9583e096909adeb0c2f66df4e10",
